	   <tr><td colspan=2>Ho, boy. 1hb = useless? No reason to train anything other than 1hs and 2hs? Laff.<br><br>SK-only 1hb weapons<br><br>MoSS- 19dmg 29dly +10int<br>Ebon Mace - 19dmg 24dly<br>Rigtorgn's Eye - 25dmg 25dly +10sta +100hp +25mana<br>Black Rock Maul of Crushing - 23dmg 23dly 15 AC +15 Int +75 HP +75 Mana<br><br>SK usable uber-1hb<br><br>Engraved Di'zok Deathbringer - 16dmg 22dly +15int +15wis proc Expel Undead (162dd vs. undead) SK PAL CLR<br>Sledge of Smashing (best ratio 1hb in the GAME after Rod of Annihilation) 27dmg 25dly 25ac +9wis +9int proc Wrath (218dd, level 29 cleric spell) SK PAL<br><br>Boy, what garbage this is, good thing you never trained 1hb, eh? While most of these are uber-drops, some (MoSS) are easily attained, relatively inexpensive (1 - 1.5k on my server), and excellent in terms of ratio.<br><br>Shall I do 2hb, now? Or perhaps piercing? I have trained all these skills except piercing, since I'm level 45 and it would be a pain to train it up. But then I'd be sorry if I got my hand on a Shard of Night (21dmg 24dly +5str +5int +5svp +5svd1hp) or a Lance of Thunder (52dmg 46dly +15wis +15int +75hp +15svm2hp), wouldn't I?<br><br>/sigh<br><br>Eitsekur<br>45 Shadow Knight (Erudite)<br>Mythrilmoon Mystics, 7th Hammer<br><br>Still not uber enough to wield most of those weapons, makes me sad.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
